cs.SI, cs.SY, cs.CY, cs.SD, cs.CE 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) - The paper focuses on the spread of epidemics in social and technological networks, which falls under the scope of this sub-category. 
2. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper presents a dynamic model to describe the movement of individuals and/or their mobile devices in an urban environment, which can be considered as a system. 
3. cs.CY (Computational Geometry) - The paper incorporates the fact that different locations can accommodate a different number of people, which can be analyzed using computational geometry techniques. 
4. cs.SD (Software Development) - The paper may involve the development of software tools to simulate and analyze the spread of epidemics in social and technological networks. 
5. cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) - The paper may involve the application of computational techniques to study the spread of epidemics in an urban environment, which can be considered as a form of computational engineering.
